race.comment: SWORD OF LEGACY (1) is a recent arrival in the Waller yard and returns from a 15-week spell. The highlight to date was a desperately close second in the Group 3 Chairmans over 1000m at Sandown last February. Trialled well at Warwick Farm recently. Has the class to take this out. PYROLYSIS (2) last appeared when she led but found one better on a heavy track at Warwick Farm in July. Trialling in great style and might go to a new level this time in work on firmer summer tracks. CHAMPERE (6) is a well-bred filly from the Hawkes stable on debut. Trials have been impressive. Must be respected. Recent Beaumont track trial winner BRROOSHA (3) is worth monitoring in betting from the Ciaron Maher stable.
